

	 
      i saw something yesterday that put me in a good mood the rest of the day: an old rich lady picking up dog poop. she was using plastic bags, one like a glove the other to deposit her treasures in. it's not like she can't afford a pooper scooper, so i wondered what that was all about. the look on her face seemed to say, "this is degrading, but this is a temporary thing, it's not like they're going to poop all the time..." which just goes to show you why owning a cat is better. i cannot imagine following an animal around in the freezing cold waiting diligently to pick up their feces. sure, i have to clean the cats' litter box, but at least it's not fresh and still steaming...
    
